description:
Small, fast-paced, Manhasset based civil litigation law firm seeks a full time paralegal/legal assistant to become part of our team! You will provide overall support to attorneys and interact directly with clients, courts, attorneys, insurance adjusters and vendors in a challenging, yet enjoyable work environment. The position offers an exciting opportunity to gain valuable experience and grow with the firm by handling a variety of matters, including Personal Injury; Landlord-Tenant disputes; Family Law; Contract Disputes; Estate Litigation, and more.

**Responsibilities include**:

* answering phone calls;
* scheduling court appearances and depositions;
* managing calendars for attorneys;
* putting together exhibits and necessary documents for motions and other court filings;
* e-filing;
* file/deadline management;
* assisting in trial preparation;
* client and attorney contact;
* various legal drafting, dependent on experience; and
* office errands.

**Qualifications:**

* Previous experience as a litigation paralegal, legal secretary, or other law firm experience preferred, but willing to train the right candidate;
* Strong work ethic, fast learner, phone and writing skills;
* Strong team player with excellent communication skils;
* Comfort on the phone;
* Ability to prioritize and multi-task, being deadline and detailed-oriented;
* Ability to speak Spanish is a strong plus but not required
* Have a car and be willing to travel outside of Nassau County, as needed and with reimbursement; and
* Proficient with Microsoft Office and legal software.

Compensation is competitive and commensurate with experience. Please respond with resume and cover letter that includes available start date and compensation requirements. Applications without these documents and information may not be considered. Kohan Law Group, PC is an equal opportunity employer.

Job Type: Full-time

Pay: $60,000.00 - $95,000.00 per year

Benefits:

* Employee discount
* Paid time off

Schedule:

* Monday to Friday

Education:

* High school or equivalent (Preferred)

Experience:

* Microsoft Office: 1 year (Preferred)

Language:

* Spanish (Preferred)

Work Location: In person
